## Summary — the one-paragraph version

All three are transformer-based large language models trained through the same broad pipeline (massive pretraining on next-token prediction, followed by instruction-tuning and preference-based fine-tuning), and they generate responses the same fundamental way: one token at a time, using self-attention to weigh the relevance of every prior token. What differs between ChatGPT, Claude, and Gemini isn't the core mechanism — it's the company behind them (OpenAI, Anthropic, Google DeepMind), their training philosophy and safety approach, their multimodal capabilities and context window sizes, their ecosystem integrations, and the tone/behavior instilled during fine-tuning. None of these differences make one "smarter" in an absolute sense — they're optimized differently for different priorities, and the right choice depends on what you're using it for.

